OL,3,CDisgraced top lawyer has appeal
OL,4,Cagainst prison sentence rejected
OL,6,FThe case was only scheduled for
OL,7,FThursday morning but rolled into the
OL,8,Fafternoon as Steenson addressed Sir
OL,9,FTimothy Le Cocq for almost four hours.
OL,11,FThe defendant told the Bailiff he
OL,12,Fbelieves that the sentence was based
OL,13,Fon the wrong facts, the Magistrate did
OL,14,Fnot believe him, was dismissive, and
OL,15,Fdid not take into account his
OL,16,Fmitigating circumstances.
